"S24 A3b shakeout: rt_alloc_slow only handled Format::Slots (D7's original
 contract), but Ir::AllocClosure (A3a) and the materialize-Context prologue
 (A3b) emit Ir::Alloc for Closure/Context klasses whose site size covers the
 VARIABLE tail. On eden overflow the slow path allocated nis words (too
 short) and the compiled continuation's stores corrupted the neighboring
 object. Debug builds aborted at the Format::Slots assert; release corrupted
 silently — surfaced as deltablue's doesNotUnderstand #value: at
 threshold=200 (only under real allocation pressure; small repros stay on
 the inline fast path — hence MACVM_EDEN=64 below to force the slow path).

 Run:    MACVM_EDEN=64 MACVM_JIT=threshold=200 macvm run <this> --world world
 Expect: s=1500 (byte-identical to MACVM_JIT=off). Pre-fix debug builds
 abort at stubs.rs rt_alloc_slow's format assert; pre-fix release builds
 corrupt the heap once any closure/Context Alloc overflows eden.

 Shape mirrors deltablue Planner>>constraintsConsuming:do: — a materialize
 method (block arg + send-result temp both ctx-captured) whose escaping
 capturing block contains a nested and:-block and value:'s the block arg."
Object subclass: Item [
    isOk [ ^true ]
]
Object subclass: CCRepro [
    marker [ ^999 ]
    consuming: coll do: aBlock [ | det |
        det := self marker.
        coll do: [:c | ((c ~~ det) and: [ c isOk ]) ifTrue: [ aBlock value: c ] ].
    ]
    run: iters [ | s coll |
        coll := OrderedCollection new.
        1 to: 5 do: [:i | coll add: Item new ].
        s := 0.
        1 to: iters do: [:i | | t |
            t := 0.
            self consuming: coll do: [:c | t := t + 1 ].
            s := s + t ].
        ^s ]
]
Transcript show: 's='; show: (CCRepro new run: 300) printString; cr.
Smalltalk quit: 0.
